A foreign businessman has been charged before a Nairobi court with alleged Sh11.1 billion tax evasion. Mr Parmar Kirit Kumar Ranchodbhai allegedly failed to declare Sh3,421,645,274 value-added tax returns to Kenya Revenue Authority(KRA) for 2015 income. Kasarani He is accused of knowingly and deliberately having committed the offence, with others not before court, on diverse dates between June 1 and December 31, 2015 at Kasarani, Nairobi. READ: Traders face Sh7bn tax evasion charges in KRA fraud crackdown The Indian national is also charged with knowingly and deliberately omitting Sh8,037,383,938 value-added tax returns to KRA for 2016 income. He allegedly committed the second charge with others not before court on diverse dates between January 1, 2016 and December 31, 2016. In the third count, Mr Parmar allegedly omitted to declare Sh237,177,262 value-added tax returns last year. Tax returns He was also charged with failure to file income tax returns by the due date with the Commissioner of Domestic Taxes for his 2015 and 2016 income as required by the law. He allegedly, being a person chargeable to tax, without reasonable cause failed to file the returns on diverse dates between June 30, 2016 and June 30 last year.